in the third grade.

06:28.329 --> 06:29.329
Goddamn memory.

06:29.397 --> 06:31.097
Stop.

06:31.165 --> 06:33.299
Look, no one's gonna suspect
you're a dealer.

06:33.367 --> 06:34.300
I mean, look at me.

06:34.368 --> 06:36.168
This is a $2,000 suit, Mike.

06:36.236 --> 06:37.636
I got, like, 12 of 'em.

06:37.704 --> 06:39.405
I take on
real software projects.

06:39.473 --> 06:44.110
I have clients who bring me
briefcases filled with cash,

06:44.178 --> 06:45.678
and I hand them
identical briefcases

06:45.746 --> 06:47.147
with vacuum-sealed bud.

06:47.215 --> 06:48.949
So what do you need me for?

06:49.017 --> 06:51.219
Well, I have a client
coming in from out of town,

06:51.287 --> 06:52.854
and I can't meet him,

06:52.922 --> 06:55.824
and I need someone I can trust
to make the drop.

06:55.892 --> 06:57.426
It's totally safe.

06:57.493 --> 06:59.161
Trevor, a person
is more likely to die

06:59.228 --> 07:00.595
while dealing drugs
than they would be

07:00.663 --> 07:02.863
on death row in Texas.

07:02.931 --> 07:04.331
Wait.
What are you talking about?

07:04.399 --> 07:05.666
It's from <i>Freakonomics.</i>

07:05.734 --> 07:06.833
Do you read anything
that I give you?

07:06.901 --> 07:08.702
It doesn't matter,

07:08.770 --> 07:10.337
because you have to find
somebody else.

07:10.404 --> 07:11.571
I'm not interested.

07:11.639 --> 07:13.740
Not interested in what?

07:13.807 --> 07:14.974
What are you doing here?
You said you were gonna stay

07:15.042 --> 07:15.975
