what makes you think

15:21.533 --> 15:23.067
that I'm gonna let
the whitest man

15:23.135 --> 15:25.269
that I have ever seen
interview for our firm?

15:25.337 --> 15:28.172
Because I have
an appointment.

15:28.240 --> 15:30.808
Hmm.

15:55.502 --> 15:56.970
You can do this.

16:12.218 --> 16:13.852
Kid, what is wrong with you?

16:13.919 --> 16:15.186
You look
like you're 11 years old.

16:15.254 --> 16:17.255
I was late to puberty.

16:20.592 --> 16:22.160
Harvey Specter.

16:47.389 --> 16:49.124
Uh, excuse me.

16:49.191 --> 16:51.259
I was thinking
about going for a swim.

16:51.327 --> 16:52.561
Are the pool facilities here
nice?

16:52.629 --> 16:53.796
Of course, sir.

16:53.863 --> 16:56.899
This is the Chilton Hotel.

16:59.569 --> 17:01.003
And do you have the time?

17:01.071 --> 17:04.071
Yes, uh...

17:04.140 --> 17:07.241
10:00.
Thanks.

17:11.246 --> 17:12.746
- He saw your gun.
- You think that's him?

17:18.986 --> 17:20.454
Matches the description.

17:20.521 --> 17:22.189
But he didn't go
in the room.

17:22.257 --> 17:23.156
It's 10:00 exactly.
He's just walking by?

17:27.430 --> 17:29.264
Go after him.
Stay on the radio.

17:50.389 --> 17:53.557
Rick Sorkin.

17:53.625 --> 17:55.960
Rick Sorkin.

17:58.897 --> 18:00.097
Rick Sorkin?

18:00.165 --> 18:02.366
Excuse me, Mr. Sorkin,

18:02.434 --> 18:03.901
you are five minutes late.

18:03.969 --> 18:05.636
Is there a reason
why I should let you in?

18:08.206 --> 18:10.241
Look, I'm just trying
to ditch the cops, okay?

18:10.308 --> 18:12.977
I don't really care
if you let me in or not.

18:21.319 --> 18:22.519
Mr. Specter will be
right with you.

18:22.587 --> 18:24.987
What?

18:25.055 --> 18:28.890
Can I get you anything?
A coffee or a bottle of water?

18:31.160 --> 18:32.961
Hi, Rick Sorkin.

18:33.029 --> 18:34.929
Harvey Specter.
Nice to meet you.

18:34.997 --> 18:37.432
Why don't you have
a seat here?

18:37.499 --> 18:39.601
Whoa.
What's this?

18:46.843 --> 18:47.776
Can I help you?

18:47.844 --> 18:50.246
No.

18:52.616 --> 18:55.351
How the hell did you know
they were the police?

18:55.419 --> 18:57.787
I read this novel
in elementary school,

18:57.855 --> 18:59.189
and it was
the exact same thing.

18:59.256 --> 19:01.891
You read a novel
in elementary school.

19:01.959 --> 19:04.160
What?
I like to read.

19:04.228 --> 19:06.595
And why'd you ask them
what time it was?

19:06.663 --> 19:07.963
Throw 'em off.

19:08.031 --> 19:09.331
What kind of drug dealer

19:09.399 --> 19:10.999
asks a cop
what time it is

19:11.067 --> 19:12.801
when he's got a briefcase
full of pot, right?

19:12.868 --> 19:15.136
We should hire you.

19:15.204 --> 19:16.938
Jesus, I'd give you
the 25 grand

19:17.005 --> 19:18.206
as a signing bonus.

19:18.273 --> 19:19.641
I'll take it.

19:19.708 --> 19:21.410
Unfortunately,

19:21.477 --> 19:23.045
we only hire
from Harvard.

19:23.112 --> 19:26.382
And you not only did not go
to Harvard Law School,

19:26.449 --> 19:28.584
you haven't even gone
to any law school.

19:28.652 --> 19:31.054
What if I told you
that I consume knowledge

19:31.121 --> 19:32.322
like no one you've ever met,

19:32.389 --> 19:34.257
and I've actually passed
the bar?

19:34.325 --> 19:37.661
I'd say
you're full of crap.

19:37.729 --> 19:40.364
That's a Barbri legal handbook
right there, right?

19:40.432 --> 19:41.999
Open it up.
Read me something.

19:42.067 --> 19:45.069
Anything.

19:48.439 --> 19:51.408
"Civil liability associated
with agency is based

19:51.475 --> 19:53.843
on several factors--"
"including the deviation

19:53.910 --> 19:55.411
"of the agent
from his path,

19:55.479 --> 19:57.379
"the reasonable inference
of agency on behalf

19:57.447 --> 19:58.513
"of the plaintiff,
and the nature

19:58.581 --> 20:01.316
of the damages themselves."

20:01.384 --> 20:03.385
How did you know that?

20:03.453 --> 20:07.257
I learned it when I studied
for the bar.

20:07.324 --> 20:11.161
Okay, hotshot,

20:11.229 --> 20:13.097
fire up this laptop.

20:13.165 --> 20:15.833
I'm gonna show you

20:15.901 --> 20:18.336
what a Harvard attorney
can do.

20:18.404 --> 20:21.539
Pick a topic.

20:21.607 --> 20:23.208
Stock option backdating.

20:23.275 --> 20:25.176
Although backdating options
is legal,

20:25.244 --> 20:27.912
violations arise
related to disclosures

20:27.980 --> 20:31.048
under IRC Section 409a.

20:31.116 --> 20:33.217
You forgot
about Sarbanes-Oxley.

20:33.285 --> 20:34.752
The statute of limitations

20:34.819 --> 20:37.354
renders Sarbanes-Oxley moot
post 2007.

20:37.422 --> 20:39.223
Not if you can find actions

20:39.290 --> 20:40.991
to cover up the violation

20:41.059 --> 20:44.662
as established in
the Sixth Circuit, May 2008.

20:44.730 --> 20:47.732
That's impressive, but you're
sitting at a computer.

20:49.067 --> 20:50.834
Playing hearts.

20:50.902 --> 20:53.604
Sorry.
If you want to beat me,

20:53.671 --> 20:55.339
you're gonna have to do it
at something else.

20:55.407 --> 20:57.207
How can you know
all that?

20:57.275 --> 20:58.742
I told you.
I like to read.

20:58.810 --> 21:01.612
And once I read something,
I understand it.

21:01.679 --> 21:04.815
And once I understand it,
I never forget it.

21:04.882 --> 21:06.450
Why take the bar?

21:08.353 --> 21:10.254
This dickhead bet me
I couldn't pass it

21:10.322 --> 21:11.455
without going to law school.

21:14.226 --> 21:16.127
Okay, look,

21:16.194 --> 21:18.329
this is
all pretty fascinating stuff,

21:18.396 --> 21:20.498
but I'm afraid
I got to get back to work.

21:20.565 --> 21:23.100
I'll make sure
that Serpico isn't around

21:23.168 --> 21:25.102
waiting for you.

21:38.616 --> 21:40.484
You want this job so much,

21:40.551 --> 21:42.385
why didn't you just go
to law school?

21:42.453 --> 21:44.787
When I was in college,

21:44.855 --> 21:46.355
it was my dream
to be a lawyer.

21:46.423 --> 21:48.824
I needed some money,

21:48.892 --> 21:50.025
and Trevor convinced me

21:50.093 --> 21:52.094
to memorize this math test

21:52.161 --> 21:56.163
and to sell it.

21:56.231 --> 21:58.332
Turns out we sold it
to the Dean's daughter.

21:58.400 --> 22:00.835
I lost my scholarship,
I got kicked out of school,

22:00.902 --> 22:05.573
I...

22:05.641 --> 22:09.044
I got knocked
into a different life.

22:09.111 --> 22:12.413
And I have been wishing
for a way back ever since.

22:16.186 --> 22:17.987
Let me tell you something.

22:18.054 --> 22:20.690
This isn't elementary school.
This is hard work.

22:20.757 --> 22:22.692
Long hours.
High pressure.

22:22.760 --> 22:24.862
I need a grown goddamn man.

22:24.929 --> 22:26.931
You give me this,

22:26.998 --> 22:28.933
and I will work
as hard as it takes

22:29.001 --> 22:30.635
to school those Harvard douches

22:30.703 --> 22:32.470
and become the best lawyer
you have ever seen.

22:32.538 --> 22:34.907
I'm inclined
to give you a shot,

22:34.974 --> 22:36.442
but what if I decide
to go another way?

22:36.510 --> 22:38.778
I'd say that's fair.

22:38.845 --> 22:40.212
Sometimes I like to hang out
with people

22:40.280 --> 22:41.981
who aren't that bright,
you know,

22:42.048 --> 22:43.148
just to see
how the other half lives.

22:43.216 --> 22:45.450
Move over.

22:45.518 --> 22:48.319
I'm emailing the firm
I just found our next associate.

22:53.558 --> 22:55.493
All right.
You're gonna start a week

22:55.494 --> 22:56.167
from Monday.

22:56.168 --> 22:57.383
Here's what you're gonna do.

22:57.384 --> 22:59.218
First, no more pot.
We drug test.

22:59.974 --> 23:01.295
Stop smoking now,
you'll be fine,

23:01.296 --> 23:02.763
I assume that's all the drugs
you do.

23:02.847 --> 23:04.548
- How do you know that?
- You read books, I read people.

23:04.970 --> 23:07.205
And potheads smoke pot.
That's what they do.

23:07.273 --> 23:09.074
It's not all I do.
I have interests.

23:09.141 --> 23:10.542
You're Albert
friggin' Einstein,

23:10.610 --> 23:12.211
and you couldn't manage
to get into law school?

23:12.279 --> 23:13.546
You think that's not
from smoking weed?

23:13.613 --> 23:14.914
- Trevor got--
- That's another thing.

23:14.981 --> 23:16.324
You're never gonna talk
to Trevor again.

23:16.325 --> 23:17.566
You're gonna ditch
that briefcase,

23:17.567 --> 23:19.129
and you're gonna get on a plane
to Harvard,

23:19.130 --> 23:20.506
and you're gonna learn
everything there is

23:20.507 --> 23:21.541
about going
to law school there.

23:21.892 --> 23:23.343
- Did you buy that suit?
- Yeah.

23:23.344 --> 23:25.045
Let's buy some new ones.

23:32.197 --> 23:35.666
Hi.

23:35.734 --> 23:38.235
How do I sign up
for today's law school tour?

23:38.302 --> 23:40.437
You go back in time
six weeks

23:40.505 --> 23:41.872
because
that's when it booked up.

23:41.940 --> 23:43.574
Um...

23:43.642 --> 23:45.943
This is Harvard Law.

23:46.011 --> 23:48.046
We get over 7,000 applications
a year.

23:48.114 --> 23:51.550
You think you can just walk in
and take a tour?

23:51.618 --> 23:53.886
Thank you.

23:53.954 --> 23:56.856
Eduardo Fernandez,
who, first of all,

23:56.924 --> 23:59.626
looks like he works
at the public pool or something,

23:59.694 --> 24:01.362
and he comes up to me
the other day,

24:01.429 --> 24:02.663
and I completely know
he's a freshman.

24:02.730 --> 24:04.064
And he looks at me
and he goes,

24:04.132 --> 24:05.299
"Where's
the public health school?"

24:05.366 --> 24:06.934
Which is right
around the corner,

24:07.001 --> 24:08.235
and you know what I tell him?
Clifford Watkins?

24:08.303 --> 24:09.904
Excuse me.

24:09.971 --> 24:10.971
Can I help you?

24:11.039 --> 24:12.706
Jonathan Atwater.

24:12.774 --> 24:14.341
I work for Dean Wormer
in the Admissions Office.

24:14.409 --> 24:16.610
Yes, of course.
What can I do for you?

24:16.678 --> 24:18.379
Well, the Dean
personally sent me down here

24:18.447 --> 24:20.681
to invite you
to a small cocktail hour

24:20.749 --> 24:24.719
for some of
our more realistic candidates.

24:24.786 --> 24:27.021
And we'd like to keep
this sort of thing discreet,

24:27.088 --> 24:29.290
so if you'd subtly hand me
your name tag,

24:29.358 --> 24:32.593
you can proceed
directly to the Dean's office.

24:32.661 --> 24:34.562
Congratulations.

24:38.466 --> 24:40.701
Harvard Law
is the oldest law school

24:40.768 --> 24:42.369
in the country
and boasts

24:42.437 --> 24:44.904
the most successful graduates
in the world.

24:44.972 --> 24:48.141
Currently, we are six
of nine Supreme Court Justices

24:48.209 --> 24:50.744
and, of course, the President
of the United States.

25:40.931 --> 25:42.598
Uh, hi, good morning.

25:42.666 --> 25:43.632
I'm here to see--
Have a seat.

25:50.139 --> 25:52.640
Thank you.

26:09.959 --> 26:11.392
Mike Ross?

26:11.460 --> 26:13.594
Hi, I'm Rachel Zane.

26:13.662 --> 26:15.663
I'll be giving you
your orientation.

26:15.730 --> 26:18.799
- Wow. You're pretty.
- Good. You've hit on me.

26:18.867 --> 26:21.201
We can get it out of the way
that I am not interested.

26:21.269 --> 26:22.336
No, I'm sorry.
I wasn't hitting on you.

26:22.403 --> 26:23.403
Trust me.

26:23.471 --> 26:25.005
I've given dozens of these,

26:25.073 --> 26:26.940
and without fail,
whatever new hotshot it is

26:27.008 --> 26:28.308
thinks that,
because I'm just a paralegal,

26:28.376 --> 26:30.076
that I will
somehow be blown away

26:30.144 --> 26:31.511
by his dazzling degree.

26:31.579 --> 26:33.814
Let me assure you,
I won't.

26:33.882 --> 26:37.352
I was.
I was hitting on you.

26:37.419 --> 26:39.187
You were.
Take notes.

26:39.255 --> 26:40.455
I'm not gonna repeat myself.

26:40.522 --> 26:43.826
I love you.

26:43.894 --> 26:46.863
The firm operates
on a chain of command model.

26:46.930 --> 26:48.465
Harvey's
your commanding officer.

26:48.532 --> 26:50.333
However, Louis Litt,
he oversees all associates,

26:50.400 --> 26:51.967
so you'll also answer
to him.

26:52.035 --> 26:53.769
What do you think
about Harvey?

26:53.837 --> 26:55.538
People are in awe of him.

26:55.606 --> 26:57.273
They say he's the best closer
there is,

26:57.341 --> 26:58.608
but I have very little contact
with him,

26:58.675 --> 26:59.809
so I don't know.

26:59.877 --> 27:02.178
And what about Louis Litt?

27:02.246 --> 27:07.316
Let's continue
with your tour.

27:07.384 --> 27:09.551
Hey, Becky.
You are glowing.

27:09.619 --> 27:11.153
I wonder why that is.
Oh, yeah.

27:11.221 --> 27:13.489
It's the day
they announce my promotion.

27:13.556 --> 27:15.058
Jimmy, have you lost weight?

27:15.126 --> 27:17.193
Steve-O.

27:17.261 --> 27:19.930
Looking like a guy
who came to work.

27:19.998 --> 27:22.233
Excuse me,
why are you scratching off

27:22.300 --> 27:23.567
the senior off my door?

27:23.635 --> 27:25.569
I got a work order
to take it off.

27:25.637 --> 27:27.571
- Who issued the work order?
- My supervisor.

27:27.639 --> 27:29.574
Why did he issue
the work order?

27:29.642 --> 27:31.576
If I knew that,
I'd be his supervisor.

27:31.643 --> 27:33.444
You seem
to be enjoying yourself.

27:33.512 --> 27:35.847
I haven't enjoyed myself
since 2004.

27:35.915 --> 27:37.682
Donna!

27:37.750 --> 27:40.251
Someone's trying to have
a little fun with me here.

27:40.318 --> 27:42.954
Jessica wants to see you
in her office.

27:43.021 --> 27:44.722
Now.

27:44.790 --> 27:50.594
And finally,
this is where you'll live.

27:50.662 --> 27:52.430
Wow.

27:52.497 --> 27:54.598
I gave you that for a reason.
You haven't taken one note.

27:54.666 --> 27:55.833
- That's because--
- Because you were

27:55.901 --> 27:57.468
too busy ogling me to listen

27:57.536 --> 27:58.769
to a word I've said?

28:01.473 --> 28:03.274
Partners' offices
anchor the wings.

28:03.342 --> 28:05.910
Fifth floor's research,
sixth is security.

28:05.977 --> 28:08.613
All work gets billed,
even if it's finding an address.

28:08.680 --> 28:09.981
I answer to Harvey

28:10.049 --> 28:11.650
and Louis Litt,
and, judging by the way

28:11.718 --> 28:13.419
you responded to my questions,

28:13.486 --> 28:16.088
I should admire Harvey
and I should fear Louis.

28:16.156 --> 28:17.790
You have been here
for five years,

28:17.857 --> 28:19.224
and just because I outrank you

28:19.292 --> 28:20.392
does not mean
I have the authority

28:20.460 --> 28:21.627
to command your services.

28:21.695 --> 28:23.062
Oh, it's also pretty clear

28:23.129 --> 28:24.497
that you think
you're too smart

28:24.564 --> 28:25.631
to be a paralegal.

28:25.699 --> 28:28.001
You know what nobody likes?

28:28.069 --> 28:29.736
Nobody likes a showoff.

28:29.804 --> 28:33.106
You used the word "ogling."

28:33.174 --> 28:35.275
When do I get
to see Harvey?

28:35.343 --> 28:37.577
Gerald Tate
fired the firm.

28:37.645 --> 28:39.780
So you're taking
my promotion away.

28:39.848 --> 28:42.649
You know, most firms would put
you in front of the bar

28:42.717 --> 28:44.284
and have your license stripped.

28:44.352 --> 28:46.086
You lied to a client,
and he figured it out.

28:46.154 --> 28:48.489
I lied to him to get him
to do the right thing

28:48.556 --> 28:50.057
and honor his goddamn contract.

28:50.125 --> 28:51.325
And you didn't seem
to mind so much

28:51.392 --> 28:52.626
when you thought
I got away with it.

28:52.694 --> 28:54.828
But you didn't get away
with it.

28:54.896 --> 28:57.265
And I can't justify handing you
a promotion

28:57.332 --> 28:58.633
on the same day that you lose
a huge client.

28:58.700 --> 29:01.269
One client
doesn't make a firm.

29:01.336 --> 29:02.771
I don't know
if you've noticed,

29:02.838 --> 29:05.140
but we're in the middle
of an economic meltdown.

29:05.208 --> 29:06.575
Companies
aren't exactly lining up

29:06.642 --> 29:08.443
to spend money
on attorneys right now.

29:08.511 --> 29:11.546
And, you know, Gerald might
have forgiven the lying

29:11.614 --> 29:13.881
had you not humiliated him.

29:13.949 --> 29:16.350
But you did,
and you need to accept that.

29:19.521 --> 29:22.423
Jessica, if you hadn't done
as much for me as you have,

29:22.490 --> 29:24.458
I'd be heading
for the door.

29:24.526 --> 29:27.194
If I hadn't done as much
for you as I have,

29:27.262 --> 29:29.062
I'd be throwing you
out the window.

29:29.130 --> 29:33.167
But, Harvey,
no more shenanigans.

29:33.234 --> 29:36.070
You do one more thing
that isn't straight as an arrow,

29:36.138 --> 29:38.139
and instead
of covering your ass,

29:38.207 --> 29:39.674
I will put you
in front of the bar myself.

29:43.480 --> 29:45.381
- Mike.
- Hey.

29:45.448 --> 29:47.950
Who's ready
for a great first day?

29:48.018 --> 29:49.852
I'm gonna have
to let you go.

29:49.920 --> 29:50.886
- What?
- I just got reamed

29:50.954 --> 29:52.488
for lying to a client,

29:52.556 --> 29:54.156
and if they find out
that I lied about you

29:54.224 --> 29:55.491
going to Harvard,
they'll take away my license.

29:55.558 --> 29:56.759
You what?

29:56.826 --> 29:59.327
Not now, Donna.

29:59.395 --> 30:00.895
Look, I have to put
my own interests

30:00.963 --> 30:02.397
above yours.
It's nothing personal.

30:02.464 --> 30:04.999
You're fired.

30:05.066 --> 30:08.468
Wait, so you're worried
that if I stay,

30:08.536 --> 30:11.805
then they might find out
that you lied about me

30:11.873 --> 30:14.208
and you'll lose your license.

30:14.276 --> 30:16.477
But if you fire me,
then I could tell them

30:16.545 --> 30:18.113
that you lied about me,

30:18.180 --> 30:19.681
and you'd definitely lose
your license.

30:19.749 --> 30:22.318
Are you telling me that

30:22.385 --> 30:23.853
if I throw you under the bus,

30:23.920 --> 30:25.287
you're gonna drag me
with you?

30:25.355 --> 30:27.323
You put your interests
above mine,

30:27.391 --> 30:30.893
and I'm just putting mine
back up next to yours.

30:33.029 --> 30:34.096
You're rehired.

30:36.600 --> 30:38.901
So should I--
all right.

30:38.968 --> 30:41.437
Here's what's gonna happen.
You're gonna give me back

30:41.504 --> 30:42.804
my promotion,
and that's the last

30:42.872 --> 30:43.972
we're gonna talk about this.

30:44.039 --> 30:45.673
And why is that?

30:45.741 --> 30:47.508
Because if you don't,
I'm gonna go across town

30:47.576 --> 30:49.343
and join Rick Peterson.

30:49.411 --> 30:51.312
I'm gonna approach every client
I've ever closed,

30:51.380 --> 30:53.181
and I'm gonna
take them with me.

30:53.248 --> 30:54.983
You do that,
and you'll force me

30:55.050 --> 30:56.551
to put you in front
of the ethics board.

30:56.619 --> 30:58.286
- I don't think you will.
- And why not?

30:58.354 --> 30:59.922
Because you were obligated
to notify them

30:59.989 --> 31:02.057
the second I lied to Gerald,
but you didn't.

31:02.125 --> 31:03.826
You put me in front
of the board right now,

31:03.894 --> 31:05.161
I'll put you right up there
with me.

31:05.229 --> 31:07.731
Hmm.

31:12.104 --> 31:16.140
I'll...I'll give you
your promotion.

31:16.208 --> 31:17.909
But you have to do something
for me.

31:17.976 --> 31:19.143
Anything.

31:19.211 --> 31:21.479
Ah.
Pro bono.

31:21.547 --> 31:22.580
Anything but that.

31:22.648 --> 31:24.149
Harvey, pro bono cases

31:24.217 --> 31:25.985
are how we, as a firm,
show that we care

31:26.052 --> 31:27.519
about more
than just ourselves.

31:27.587 --> 31:29.788
I'm not saying
we shouldn't do them.

31:29.856 --> 31:31.290
I'm saying
I shouldn't do them.

31:31.357 --> 31:32.858
And it's how you can show me

31:32.926 --> 31:35.360
that you care about more
than just yourself.

31:35.428 --> 31:37.663
You'll handle this yourself.

31:37.731 --> 31:39.031
You will not pass it off.

31:39.099 --> 31:41.633
Absolutely.

31:44.638 --> 31:46.039
Your first case.

31:46.106 --> 31:47.073
Awesome.
What is it?

31:47.141 --> 31:48.075
Pro bono.

31:48.142 --> 31:49.677
Sexual harassment.

31:49.744 --> 31:51.779
Don't tell anyone
I laid it off on you,

31:51.846 --> 31:53.614
and don't screw it up.
Got it.

31:53.682 --> 31:56.651
You can't handle it.
I'll knock it out of the park.

31:56.718 --> 31:58.753
Easy, Clarence Thomas.
Just go meet the client.

31:58.821 --> 32:01.857
Hey. Didn't I tell you
to get some better suits?

32:01.925 --> 32:03.959
I spent $500.

32:04.027 --> 32:05.895
For how many suits?

32:05.963 --> 32:08.197
Five.

32:08.265 --> 32:09.598
What?

32:09.666 --> 32:11.200
Nancy?

32:11.268 --> 32:12.868
- Mike?
- Yeah, hi.

32:15.105 --> 32:17.173
You're a kid.

32:17.240 --> 32:19.241
No, I'm a--
I'm a grown man.

32:19.309 --> 32:22.044
You're so skinny.
Have a grape.

32:22.112 --> 32:24.747
Thank you.

32:24.814 --> 32:26.782
Why don't you tell me
your story?

32:26.849 --> 32:28.483
It started two years ago.

32:28.551 --> 32:29.951
I was a stay-at-home mom

32:30.019 --> 32:31.920
to my son, Freddie.

32:31.987 --> 32:33.821
And one day
we were at little league,

32:33.889 --> 32:35.456
Freddie was five.

32:35.523 --> 32:36.890
He really hated
that he couldn't play

32:36.958 --> 32:38.292
with the older kids.

32:38.359 --> 32:40.860
It was the third inning,
and I got a phone call.

32:40.928 --> 32:42.195
My husband had been
in a car accident,

32:42.263 --> 32:45.264
and he was gone,
just like that.

32:45.332 --> 32:47.633
I'm so sorry.

32:47.701 --> 32:50.737
I did the best I could.

32:50.805 --> 32:52.606
I got myself a job
as a secretary

32:52.673 --> 32:53.974
at Devlin McGreggor.

32:54.041 --> 32:55.242
And I even got promoted

32:55.309 --> 32:56.510
to secretary of the president,

32:56.577 --> 32:58.612
Charles Hunt.

32:58.680 --> 33:01.749
And that's
when it all changed.

33:01.816 --> 33:04.151
It's okay.
Tell me what happened.

33:04.219 --> 33:06.387
He started asking me
to stay late,

33:06.455 --> 33:09.557
order in dinners together,
stuff like that.

33:09.625 --> 33:11.927
One night, he says
that if I sleep with him,

33:11.995 --> 33:13.362
he's gonna take care of me
in the firm,

33:13.429 --> 33:15.964
and, if I don't,
he's gonna fire me.

33:16.032 --> 33:17.199
So what did you do?

33:17.267 --> 33:18.534
I went to Human Resources.

33:18.602 --> 33:20.503
They said they investigated,

33:20.571 --> 33:22.972
couldn't find anything
to support my claim.

33:23.040 --> 33:24.507
Two months later,
I was fired

33:24.575 --> 33:26.276
for poor job performance.

33:26.344 --> 33:27.945
They wouldn't let me
say good-bye to anybody.

33:28.012 --> 33:30.314
They wouldn't write me
a letter of recommendation.

33:30.382 --> 33:31.983
I wasn't looking
for a payoff.

33:32.050 --> 33:34.451
All I wanted
was for it to stop.

33:34.519 --> 33:36.386
Can you help me?

33:36.454 --> 33:39.389
Uh, yes.

33:39.457 --> 33:41.791
Yes, I can.

33:41.859 --> 33:43.326
What do you need
my help for?

33:43.394 --> 33:45.428
- Wait, can I just--
- No, give me the update.

33:45.495 --> 33:47.730
You know,
she's a nice woman.

33:47.798 --> 33:49.165
She--
On the case.

33:49.233 --> 33:50.633
I don't get
emotionally attached

33:50.701 --> 33:52.034
to the client.

33:52.102 --> 33:53.837
This woman had
her life ripped apart.

33:53.905 --> 33:55.439
You don't even care?

33:55.507 --> 33:57.141
I'm not about caring.
I'm about winning.

33:57.209 --> 33:59.010
Why can't you be
about both?

33:59.077 --> 34:00.578
I'd explain it to you,

34:00.646 --> 34:03.881
but then I'd have
to care about you.

34:03.949 --> 34:05.516
What are you doing?

34:05.584 --> 34:06.751
Don't touch that.

34:06.818 --> 34:08.518
I'm just checking my lock.

34:08.587 --> 34:11.688
You ride your bike to...

34:11.757 --> 34:12.724
It's locked, okay?

34:12.791 --> 34:14.324
Come on.

34:19.398 --> 34:21.299
Defense sent over
the investigation files

34:21.367 --> 34:22.900
as a courtesy.
No, they didn't.

34:22.967 --> 34:24.369
Nobody does anything
as a courtesy.

34:24.437 --> 34:26.004
They sent those files

34:26.072 --> 34:27.205
because that's
where they want you to look.

34:27.273 --> 34:28.507
Listen, being a lawyer's

34:28.574 --> 34:30.475
like being a doctor.

34:30.543 --> 34:31.876
You mean how you don't get
emotional about the client?

34:31.944 --> 34:34.079
No, I mean you keep pressing
until it hurts.

34:34.146 --> 34:35.580
Then you know
where to look.

34:35.648 --> 34:37.315
Forget about impeaching
the investigation.

34:37.382 --> 34:39.117
It won't lead anywhere.
No employee's gonna testify

34:39.185 --> 34:40.618
against their own CEO.
Okay.

34:40.686 --> 34:42.487
So what do you suggest I do?

34:42.554 --> 34:44.556
Think.
This guy's done this once...

34:44.623 --> 34:46.357
He's done it before.

34:46.425 --> 34:47.792
And if the people
who work for him now

34:47.860 --> 34:49.293
won't testify against him...

34:49.360 --> 34:51.896
Someone who used
to work for him might.

34:51.964 --> 34:53.397
You know what,

34:53.465 --> 34:55.099
I'd subpoena
the personnel records

34:55.167 --> 34:56.634
of every woman
who's left the firm

34:56.702 --> 34:58.203
during this guy's tenure.
That's funny.

34:58.270 --> 34:59.804
That's exactly what I thought.

34:59.872 --> 35:01.339
Then what do you need
my help for?

35:01.407 --> 35:03.808
I don't know
how to fill out a subpoena.

35:03.876 --> 35:08.680
Figure it out yourself.

35:08.747 --> 35:10.882
Donna, can you show me
how to fill out a subpoena?

35:10.950 --> 35:12.450
Absolutely.
And after that,

35:12.518 --> 35:13.985
you want me to show you
how to wipe your ass?

35:14.053 --> 35:15.052
It's funny,
because you should already know

35:15.120 --> 35:16.420
how to do both those things.

35:16.488 --> 35:18.322
Ha, yeah,
that's hilarious.

35:18.390 --> 35:20.425
What's that?
That's my suit guy.

35:20.492 --> 35:22.627
Go in, tell him I sent you,
and spend some money.

35:22.694 --> 35:25.063
What does it matter
how much money I spend on suits?

35:25.131 --> 35:26.665
People respond
to how we're dressed,

35:26.733 --> 35:28.233
so like it or not,
this is what you have to do.

35:28.301 --> 35:30.235
That's weird,
you giving me advice.

35:30.303 --> 35:32.671
It sounds like you actually care
about me.

35:32.738 --> 35:34.539
I don't.
You're a reflection of me,

35:34.607 --> 35:36.342
and I absolutely
care about me.

35:36.409 --> 35:38.677
So get your skinny tie
out of my face and get to work.

35:41.381 --> 35:42.981
That was a little harsh.

35:43.049 --> 35:44.549
Really?

35:44.617 --> 35:47.318
Yeah.

35:53.392 --> 35:55.492
Mike.

35:55.560 --> 35:57.561
Where are you going?

35:57.629 --> 36:00.263
It's 6:30.
I'm going home.

36:01.566 --> 36:03.099
Okay.
What's so funny?

36:03.167 --> 36:04.734
You're a rookie associate.

36:04.801 --> 36:07.269
If you go home before 9:00
on your first week,

36:07.337 --> 36:09.405
you're not gonna make it
through your first month.

36:09.472 --> 36:10.872
And Louis Litt
wants to see you.

36:10.940 --> 36:12.875
- Hey, can I ask you something?
- Mm-hmm.

36:12.943 --> 36:15.411
This tie,
is it too skinny?

36:15.478 --> 36:16.645
Yeah.

36:16.713 --> 36:19.715
Right.

36:19.782 --> 36:21.683
Yeah.

36:29.393 --> 36:31.494
I know you had orientation
from Rachel,

36:31.561 --> 36:35.365
but I wanted to give you
a special welcome from me.

36:35.432 --> 36:39.703
Amongst other things,
I'm sort of the disciplinarian

36:39.770 --> 36:40.704
of the associates.

36:44.442 --> 36:46.009
- You wanted to see me?
- Yes.

36:46.077 --> 36:48.478
Gary, please come in.
Mike, this is Gary Lipsky.

36:48.546 --> 36:50.413
Gary's one of our most promising
associates from last year.

36:50.480 --> 36:52.181
Hi.

36:52.249 --> 36:54.951
Gary, Ms. Pearson
wanted me to ask,

36:55.019 --> 36:56.486
have you completed
the Petramco filing?

36:56.553 --> 36:58.187
Well, my brother was in
over the weekend,

36:58.255 --> 36:59.389
so I didn't really get
to it.

36:59.456 --> 37:01.157
Look, I mean,
Gary, come on.

37:01.225 --> 37:02.325
This is, like, the third time
I've had to ask.

37:02.393 --> 37:03.793
I'll get right on it.

37:03.861 --> 37:05.562
Don't bother.
You're fired.

37:05.629 --> 37:07.497
What?
You can't fire me.

37:07.565 --> 37:09.132
Oh, yes, I can.
And I just did.

37:09.199 --> 37:11.834
Go pack up your things.

37:11.902 --> 37:14.070
Don't you ever show your face
in this place again.

37:20.644 --> 37:23.313
See, I arranged
for you to see that

37:23.381 --> 37:25.849
because we pay our associates
very well

37:25.917 --> 37:28.685
and we provide the opportunity
for unlimited advancement.

37:28.753 --> 37:32.189
But in return
we expect results.

37:34.693 --> 37:36.895
Have I made myself clear?

37:36.963 --> 37:39.130
Yeah.

37:41.167 --> 37:43.035
Great.

37:43.103 --> 37:45.137
Welcome to Pearson Hardman.

37:50.277 --> 37:53.512
Feel free
to go back to work.

37:56.115 --> 37:58.149
Harvey.

37:58.217 --> 38:01.286
Okay, I have two words
for you.

38:01.353 --> 38:03.988
Absolutely beautiful.

38:04.056 --> 38:06.491
You think you're the only one
who can charm a client?

38:06.559 --> 38:09.327
Categorically stunning.

38:09.394 --> 38:11.362
How's the new kid
working out?

38:11.430 --> 38:13.531
Regally hot.

38:13.599 --> 38:16.234
- You're an idiot.
- Jessica Pearson.

38:16.301 --> 38:18.302
Good night, Harvey.

38:26.145 --> 38:27.312
What are you doing here?

38:27.379 --> 38:29.815
Watching <i>Sportscenter.</i>

38:29.882 --> 38:32.484
Boo-yah.

38:32.552 --> 38:33.886
You won't return
my phone calls.

38:33.953 --> 38:36.054
Ah, yeah,
because you set me up.

38:36.122 --> 38:38.290
Do you remember that?
You think I knew about that?

38:38.358 --> 38:41.059
Here we go.
Round 50 of I get the shaft

38:41.127 --> 38:43.262
because you didn't know
the whole story.

38:43.329 --> 38:45.063
You knew there were risks
when you quoted that crap

38:45.131 --> 38:46.332
from that book.

38:46.399 --> 38:47.966
Okay, you needed money,

38:48.034 --> 38:49.368
and I came through
with an opportunity

38:49.435 --> 38:51.236
like always.

38:51.304 --> 38:52.304
Besides, you weren't
the only one who got screwed.

38:52.372 --> 38:53.706
They pulled a gun on me.

38:53.774 --> 38:54.807
Oh, really?

38:54.875 --> 38:56.175
And why did they do that?

38:56.242 --> 38:57.442
To keep me from warning you.

38:57.510 --> 38:59.111
So you did know.

38:59.179 --> 39:00.613
Well, not until
after it was too late.

39:00.681 --> 39:02.214
Well, it's too late now.

39:02.282 --> 39:04.050
Look, let me
make it up to you.

39:04.117 --> 39:05.718
Oh, you want
to make it up to me?

39:05.786 --> 39:08.620
Give me my key back.

39:15.462 --> 39:18.197
Michael.

39:18.264 --> 39:20.299
Come on.

39:20.366 --> 39:21.534
You know I don't want
to live in a world

39:21.601 --> 39:23.735
where we're not tight.

39:24.904 --> 39:27.539
Then kill yourself.

39:27.607 --> 39:29.140
Get out.

39:30.776 --> 39:33.778
Get the hell out.

39:57.962 --> 39:59.363
Donna, I need the--

39:59.430 --> 40:01.180
oh, also I didn't have
a chance to--

40:01.664 --> 40:03.232
marry me?
I took care of that too.

40:03.299 --> 40:04.900
We've been married
for the last seven years.

40:04.968 --> 40:07.002
Excellent.

40:07.070 --> 40:09.604
Umm, Devlin McGreggor's
fighting the subpoena.

40:09.672 --> 40:11.272
They filed a motion
to dismiss the case

40:11.340 --> 40:12.741
based on our
lack of evidence.

40:12.808 --> 40:14.209
- Good.
- Good.

40:14.277 --> 40:15.776
Wait, what do you mean,
"good"?

40:15.844 --> 40:17.211
They don't want
to hand over the files.

40:17.279 --> 40:18.680
You pressed where it hurt.

40:18.747 --> 40:20.215
You're looking
in the right place.

40:20.282 --> 40:21.449
Did you think
they wouldn't fight back?

40:21.517 --> 40:23.184
Well, I--
now that you mention it.

40:23.252 --> 40:24.652
Oh, my bad.

40:24.720 --> 40:26.020
I keep forgetting

40:26.088 --> 40:27.421
you don't
actually know anything.

40:27.489 --> 40:29.123
The idea is,

40:29.191 --> 40:30.925
you make a move,
they make a move.

40:30.993 --> 40:32.593
You go back and forth
until one of you wins.

40:32.661 --> 40:34.195
Okay, what if they win
the motion

40:34.262 --> 40:36.063
and the case
gets dismissed?

40:36.131 --> 40:38.432
You're not as good
as you think you are.

40:40.235 --> 40:41.569
Harvey.
What a coincidence.

40:41.637 --> 40:43.238
I was wondering
how the pro bono was coming.

40:43.305 --> 40:44.305
I'm all over it.

40:44.373 --> 40:45.606
That makes me very happy,

40:45.674 --> 40:47.241
because if I were
to find out

40:47.309 --> 40:48.476
that you weren't putting in
your full effort,

40:48.543 --> 40:49.744
I'd be very upset.

40:49.811 --> 40:52.146
No worries.
We're all good.

41:00.756 --> 41:02.890
Rachel! Rachel, Rachel,
Rachel. I need your help.

41:02.958 --> 41:04.258
There's a hearing
on my subpoena.

41:04.326 --> 41:05.827
I've got three cases
in front of you,

41:05.894 --> 41:06.828
so you're gonna have
to wait in line.

41:06.895 --> 41:07.895
No. No, no, no.

41:07.963 --> 41:09.497
My hearing is tomorrow.

41:09.564 --> 41:10.832
So why are you
coming to me?

41:10.899 --> 41:13.634
Because Donna says

41:13.702 --> 41:15.036
you're the best researcher
in the firm.

41:15.104 --> 41:18.005
Let me see the motion.

41:18.073 --> 41:20.375
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

41:20.442 --> 41:22.176
You have an office?

41:22.244 --> 41:24.912
How do you have an office
and I have a cubicle?

41:24.980 --> 41:27.114
Like you said,
I'm the best researcher

41:27.182 --> 41:28.949
in the firm.
Really?

41:29.017 --> 41:30.517
I just made that up.

41:30.585 --> 41:32.986
I didn't even have time
to talk to Donna.

41:33.054 --> 41:36.055
Is this all a joke
to you?

41:36.123 --> 41:37.257
'Cause I take my job seriously.

41:37.324 --> 41:38.725
No, I'm sorry.

41:38.792 --> 41:41.161
Look, I was--

41:41.228 --> 41:43.631
look, you weren't there,
okay.

41:43.699 --> 41:46.000
I care about this woman.

41:46.068 --> 41:48.136
She's got
nowhere else to turn--

41:48.204 --> 41:49.638
And you can't help her
by yourself.

41:49.706 --> 41:51.940
I can.

41:52.008 --> 41:54.843
I just prefer not to.

41:54.911 --> 41:58.347
Okay.

41:58.415 --> 41:59.748
You're asking to look
at private files

41:59.816 --> 42:01.183
without any evidence
of your assertion.

42:01.251 --> 42:02.351
Yeah, but the only way
that we can find

42:02.418 --> 42:04.152
the evidence is to look
at those files.

42:04.220 --> 42:05.153
It's a rickety argument.

42:05.221 --> 42:07.322
But is there a precedent?

42:07.390 --> 42:11.126
Let's go see
if we can find one.

42:11.194 --> 42:13.695
Research is as much art
as science,

42:13.763 --> 42:16.398
so we're gonna look
at privacy and harassment law

42:16.465 --> 42:18.767
so you can find a combination
of cases

42:18.834 --> 42:20.568
to make an argument.
I'll take privacy.

42:20.636 --> 42:22.203
I'll take harassment law.

42:22.271 --> 42:23.772
This'll take a while.

42:23.840 --> 42:25.441
We're gonna need dinner.

42:25.509 --> 42:27.577
- Chinese.
- No.

42:27.645 --> 42:29.012
I can afford Chinese
on my own.

42:29.079 --> 42:30.813
This is on the firm.
I want Sushi.

42:30.881 --> 42:32.516
Ooh.

42:32.583 --> 42:34.718
So they told me to put
my top investigator on it.

42:34.786 --> 42:37.021
- What did you do?
- What could I do?

42:37.089 --> 42:38.789
You were out of the country,
I gave them Luderman.

42:40.626 --> 42:42.026
By the way,
that dress...

42:42.094 --> 42:43.361
What, this old thing?
Come on.

42:43.428 --> 42:45.463
Beautiful.

42:45.531 --> 42:47.265
Vanessa, why don't we do this
more often?

42:47.333 --> 42:50.267
'Cause it always ends
the same way.

42:50.335 --> 42:52.470
Then why are we
doing it now?

42:52.537 --> 42:54.939
Harvey,
I don't sleep around.

42:55.006 --> 42:57.374
And I could never be
in a relationship with you.

42:57.442 --> 42:59.610
All you ever think about
is yourself.

42:59.678 --> 43:02.245
I'm thinking about you and me
right now.

43:06.384 --> 43:07.919
Please.
I insist.

43:07.987 --> 43:09.120
But I'm a gentleman.

43:09.188 --> 43:11.289
Besides, you came through

43:11.357 --> 43:13.192
on Dockery for me,
and I'm not one

43:13.259 --> 43:15.094
to forget a favor.

43:15.162 --> 43:17.096
Neither am I.

43:23.237 --> 43:25.905
Mr. Dockery,
you naughty, naughty boy.

43:30.944 --> 43:34.147
You remember when I said
you thought you were too smart

43:34.215 --> 43:35.448
to be a paralegal?
Mm-hmm.

43:35.516 --> 43:37.550
- Why...
- Aren't I a lawyer?

43:37.618 --> 43:39.619
Mm.

43:39.686 --> 43:42.221
I don't test well.
What?

43:42.289 --> 43:44.324
I am smart.

43:44.391 --> 43:45.959
And I know
I'd be a good lawyer.

43:46.026 --> 43:47.394
I just--I don't know
what it is.

43:47.461 --> 43:48.361
I can't take tests,

43:48.429 --> 43:51.397
and I bombed the LSATs.

43:51.465 --> 43:52.832
And even if I could get

43:52.900 --> 43:54.033
into law school,
there's no way

43:54.101 --> 43:55.969
I'd pass the bar.

43:56.036 --> 44:00.573
So if only there was someone
who could take the test for me.

44:00.641 --> 44:02.942
- Yeah, if only there were.
- Yeah.

44:03.010 --> 44:05.813
Hi. Where are you at
with the research

44:05.880 --> 44:08.215
for tomorrow's hearing?
Nothing yet.

44:08.282 --> 44:09.216
You say you care
about the client,

44:09.284 --> 44:10.651
but if you keep playing footsie

44:10.719 --> 44:12.253
instead of finding me
an argument,

44:12.320 --> 44:13.954
the client's gonna lose.

44:14.022 --> 44:15.523
I don't want to lose.

44:15.591 --> 44:17.758
Ugh.

44:17.826 --> 44:21.228
Look, it's no use.

44:21.296 --> 44:23.631
Okay, their investigation's
by the book.

